[[File:Greenhouse_Effect_zh-hans.svg|350px]]
'''溫室效应'''是指[[行星|行星]]的[[大氣層|大氣層]]因為吸收辐射能量，使得行星表面升溫的效应。由於溫室效应，行星表面溫度會比沒有大氣層時的溫度要高<ref name="ipccar4syr">{{cite web|url=http://www.ipcc.ch/publications_and_data/ar4/syr/en/annexessglossary-e-i.html|title=Annex II Glossary|publisher=Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change|accessdate=2016-08-20|archive-date=2018-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181103000935/http://www.ipcc.ch/publications_and_data/ar4/syr/en/annexessglossary-e-i.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ipcc-AR4WG1">A concise description of the greenhouse effect is given in the ''Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change Fourth Assessment Report,'' "What is the Greenhouse Effect?" [http://www.ipcc.ch/publications_and_data/ar4/wg1/en/faq-1-3.html FAQ 1.3 - AR4 WGI Chapter 1: Historical Overview of Climate Change Science] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ipcc.ch/publications_and_data/ar4/wg1/en/faq-1-3.html|date=20181130152334}}, IIPCC Fourth Assessment Report, Chapter 1, page 115: "To balance the absorbed incoming [solar] energy, the Earth must, on average, radiate the same amount of energy back to space. Because the Earth is much colder than the Sun, it radiates at much longer wavelengths, primarily in the infrared part of the spectrum (see Figure 1). Much of this thermal radiation emitted by the land and ocean is absorbed by the atmosphere, including clouds, and reradiated back to Earth. This is called the greenhouse effect."<br />
Stephen H. Schneider, in ''Geosphere-biosphere Interactions and Climate,'' Lennart O. Bengtsson and Claus U. Hammer, eds., Cambridge University Press, 2001, ISBN 0-521-78238-4, pp. 90-91.<br />
E. Claussen, V. A. Cochran, and D. P. Davis, ''Climate Change: Science, Strategies, & Solutions,'' University of Michigan, 2001. p. 373.<br />
A. Allaby and M. Allaby, ''A Dictionary of Earth Sciences,'' Oxford University Press, 1999, ISBN 0-19-280079-5, p. 244.</ref>。以往認為其機制類似[[溫室|溫室]]使其中氣溫上昇的機制，故名為「溫室效应」。不少研究指出，人为因素使地球上的温室效应異常加劇，而造成[[全球暖化|全球暖化]]的效应。

<!--原理-->
[[太阳辐射|太阳辐射]]主要是因為[[短波|短波]]辐射，然而[[地球長波輻射|地面辐射]]和大气辐射則是[[长波|长波]]辐射。大气对长波辐射的吸收力较强，对短波辐射的吸收力较弱。白天時，[[太阳|太阳]]光照射到[[地球|地球]]上，部分能量被大气吸收，部分被反射回宇宙，大約47%的能量被[[地球|地球]]表面吸收。晚上地球表面以[[红外线|红外线]]的方式向宇宙散发白天吸收的热量，其中也有部分被大气吸收。

[[大气层|大气层]]像覆盖玻璃的温室一样，保存了一定的热量，使得[[地球|地球]]不至于像没有大气层的[[月球|月球]]一样，被[[太阳|太阳]]照射时温度急剧升高，不受太阳照射时温度急剧下降。一些理論認為，由於[[溫室氣體|溫室氣體]]的增加，使[[地球|地球]]整體所保留的熱能增加，導致[[全球暖化|全球暖化]]。

<!--影響-->
如果沒有溫室效應，地球就會冷得不適合人類居住。據估計，如果沒有大氣層，地球表面平均溫度會是−18℃<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weather.gov.hk/climate_change/global_warming_c.htm#green_house_effect |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070926222008/http://www.weather.gov.hk/climate_change/global_warming_c.htm |title=甚麼是全球氣候變化？它的影響又如何？ |publisher=香港天文台 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2007-09-26 |accessdate=2016-08-19 |language=zh-hant }}</ref>。正是有了温室效应，使地球平均温度维持在15℃，然而当下过多的温室气体导致地球平均温度高于15℃。

目前，人類活動使大氣中[[温室气体|温室气体]]含量增加，由於燃燒[[化石燃料|化石燃料]]及[[水蒸氣|水蒸氣]]、[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]、[[甲烷|甲烷]]等產生排放的氣體，經紅外線輻射吸收留住能量，導致全球表面溫度升高<ref>{{cite web|language=zh-hant|url=http://www.cwb.gov.tw/V7/climate/climate_info/climate_change/change_6/change_6-3.html|title=什麼是溫室效應?|publisher=交通部中央气象局|accessdate=2016-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827193704/http://www.cwb.gov.tw/V7/climate/climate_info/climate_change/change_6/change_6-3.html|archive-date=2016-08-27|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，加劇溫室效應，造成全球暖化。为了解決此問題，[[联合国|联合国]]制定了[[联合国气候变化框架公约|气候变化框架公约]]，控制温室气体的排放量，防止地球的溫度上升，影響生態和環境。

== 歷史 ==
<!--{{Main|History of climate change science}}-->
[[约瑟夫·傅里叶|约瑟夫·傅里叶]]在1824年就提出有[[溫室氣體|溫室氣體]]存在的想法，1827年時{{le|克勞德·普雷特|Claude Pouillet}}也加強了此論點，並在1838年提出相關的證據，1859年時{{le|約翰·廷德爾|John Tyndall}}也用實驗數據驗證<ref>John Tyndall, ''[https://archive.org/details/heatconsideredas00tynduoft Heat considered as a Mode of Motion]'' (500 pages; year 1863, 1873)</ref>。1896年時[[斯凡特·奥古斯特·阿伦尼乌斯|斯凡特·奥古斯特·阿伦尼乌斯]]也確認了此一效應<ref name=anrev>{{cite journal
 | journal = Annual Review of Energy and the Environment
 | title = Water Vapor Feedback and Global Warming
 | author1 = Isaac M. Held
 | author2 = Brian J. Soden
 | volume = 25
 | publisher = Annual Reviews
 | pages = 441–475
 | doi = 10.1146/annurev.energy.25.1.441
 | date = 2000-11-01
 | url = http://arjournals.annualreviews.org/doi/full/10.1146/annurev.energy.25.1.441
 | access-date = 2016-08-11
 | archive-date = 2020-07-22
 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200722145743/https://www.annualreviews.org/doi/full/10.1146/annurev.energy.25.1.441
 | dead-url = no
 }}</ref>
。不過這些科學家都沒有用「溫室效應」來描述此一現象，一直到1901年{{le|尼尔斯·古斯塔夫·埃科赫姆|Nils Gustaf Ekholm}}才開始使用此一名詞<ref>{{cite web|last1=Easterbrook|first1=Steve|title=Who first coined the term "Greenhouse Effect"?|url=http://www.easterbrook.ca/steve/2015/08/who-first-coined-the-term-greenhouse-effect/|website=Serendipity|accessdate=11 November 2015|archive-date=2015-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151113131713/http://www.easterbrook.ca/steve/2015/08/who-first-coined-the-term-greenhouse-effect/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=Ekholm N |doi=10.1002/qj.49702711702 |title=On The Variations Of The Climate Of The Geological And Historical Past And Their Causes |journal=Quarterly Journal of the Royal Meteorological Society |volume=27 |number=117 |pages=1–62 |url=http://doi.wiley.com/10.1002/qj.49702711702 |year=1901 |access-date=2016-08-11 |archive-date=2020-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200722145743/https://rmets.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/qj.49702711702 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

1917年時[[亚历山大·格拉汉姆·贝尔|亚历山大·格拉汉姆·贝尔]]提到「（未檢測到的化石燃料燃燒）會造成類似溫室的效應」<ref name="DictionaryOfCanBiography">{{cite DCB |first=Lawrence |last=Surtees |title=Bell, Alexander Graham |url=http://www.biographi.ca/en/bio/bell_alexander_graham_15E.html |volume=15 |access-date=September 17, 2015}}</ref><ref name="G&W">Grosvenor, Edwin S. and Morgan Wesson. ''Alexander Graham Bell: The Life and Times of the Man Who Invented the Telephone''. New York: Harry N. Abrahms, Inc., 1997, p. 274, ISBN 0-8109-4005-1.</ref>。因此贝尔也倡導其他的替代能源，例如[[太陽能|太陽能]]<ref name="G&W3">Grosvenor and Wesson, 1997, p. 269.</ref>。

== 機制 ==
地球會吸收太陽釋放的电磁波辐射如[[紫外線|紫外線]]、[[可見光|可見光]]以及[[紅外線|近紅外線]]。在大氣層上端可接收到的所有輻射能中，大氣和雲會反射26%的能量到太空中，而大氣和雲本身會吸收19%的能量。大部份剩下的能量都是由地球表面吸收，因為地表的溫度比太陽要冷很多，因此其釋放的[[遠紅外線|遠紅外線]]波長也比太陽釋放的電磁波波長要长很多。大部份的熱輻射是由大氣吸收，大氣溫度會因此提高，大氣除了吸收太陽釋放的電磁波以及地球的熱輻射外，大氣也會由地面的顯熱和潛熱通量接收到能量。大氣會往上方及下方輻射能量，部份往下方輻射的能量是由地表吸收，因此地表溫度會較沒有大氣時的地表溫度要高。

[[Image:Solar_Spectrum.png|thumb]]頻譜的差異]]

一個理想熱傳導性的[[黑体_(物理学)|黑體]]若位在地球的位置，接收到太陽輻射的熱量，其溫度大約會是5.3 °C。不過因為地球反射掉約30%的太陽輻射能量<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/planetary/factsheet/earthfact.html |title=NASA Earth Fact Sheet |publisher=Nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov |accessdate=2010-10-15 |archive-date=2010-10-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101030234253/http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/planetary/factsheet/earthfact.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=harvard>{{cite web |url=http://acmg.seas.harvard.edu/people/faculty/djj/book/bookchap7.html |title=Introduction to Atmospheric Chemistry, by Daniel J. Jacob, Princeton University Press, 1999. Chapter 7, "The Greenhouse Effect" |publisher=Acmg.seas.harvard.edu |accessdate=2010-10-15 |archive-date=2010-10-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101003035132/http://acmg.seas.harvard.edu/people/faculty/djj/book/bookchap7.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，其理想[[有效溫度|有效溫度]]（使黑體輻射熱量和其吸收熱量相同的溫度）應該是−18 °C<ref>{{cite web |url=http://eesc.columbia.edu/courses/ees/climate/lectures/radiation/ |title=Solar Radiation and the Earth's Energy Balance |publisher=Eesc.columbia.edu |accessdate=2010-10-15 }}{{Dead link}}</ref><ref name="IPCC4_ch01">[http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar4/wg1/ar4-wg1-chapter1.pdf  Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change Fourth Assessment Report. Chapter 1: Historical overview of climate change science] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar4/wg1/ar4-wg1-chapter1.pdf |date=20110706234727 }} page 97</ref>。上述假想星球的表面溫度（−18 °C）較地球的平均表面溫度14 °C低了約33 °C<ref>The elusive "absolute surface air temperature," see [http://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/abs_temp.html GISS discussion] {{Wayback|url=http://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/abs_temp.html |date=20150905093320 }}</ref>。

上述基礎的機制可以用許多方式來量化，而且這些方式都不會影響基礎機制。靠近地面的大氣不會吸收熱輻射（但在對應溫室效應的波長段例外），大部份來自地表的熱損失是因為[[顯熱|顯熱]]及[[潛熱|潛熱]]的傳播。在大氣中的高度越高，因為水蒸氣（一種重要的溫室氣體）的濃度降低，因此其輻射的熱損失會越大。可以將温室效应視為在[[對流層|對流層]]中段加上一個「表面」，該表面的特性再根據[[氣溫垂直遞減率|氣溫垂直遞減率]]來調整。這個簡單的模型是假設溫度是在穩態的條件，不過實際的溫度會因為{{le|晝夜週期|diurnal cycle}}、季節週期及氣候的變化而變化。在晚上，因為大氣的放射率較低，大氣溫度會較低，但變化不大。{{le|晝夜溫度變化|Diurnal temperature variation}}會隨著高度而遞減。

在輻射效應比較顯著的區域中，也就比較接近上述理想溫室效應描述的情形。地球表面的溫度約為255 K，會以發射長波的[[紅外線|紅外線]]，波長約在 4–100 μm<ref name="Mitchell-1989">{{cite journal|doi=10.1029/RG027i001p00115|last=Mitchell|first=John F. B.|date=1989|title=THE "GREENHOUSE" EFFECT AND CLIMATE CHANGE|journal=Reviews of Geophysics|publisher=American Geophysical Union|volume=27|issue=1|pages=115–139|url=http://astrosun2.astro.cornell.edu/academics/courses/astro202/Mitchell_GRL89.pdf|accessdate=2008-03-23|bibcode=1989RvGeo..27..115M|archive-date=2011-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110615024949/http://astrosun2.astro.cornell.edu/academics/courses/astro202/Mitchell_GRL89.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。溫室氣體對入射的太陽輻射是透明的（不吸收也不會反射），但會吸收此波長下的能量<ref name="Mitchell-1989"/>。有溫室氣體的每一層大氣層都會吸收一些由下方所發射的能量，再往上方及下方再發射，發射能量和吸收能量達到平衡。因此越下方的大氣越溫暖。若增加溫室氣體的濃度也就增加了吸收及再發射的能量，因此會使大氣層更溫暖，最後也會使地面變溫暖<ref name="IPCC4_ch01" />。

溫室氣體－包括大部份由二種不同原子組成的雙原子氣體（例如一氧化碳）以及所有由三個或多個原子組成的氣體－可以吸收及發射紅外線輻射。雖然乾燥大氣中有99%（氧氣、氮氣及氬氣）都不會吸收及發射紅外線，不過分子間的碰撞使得溫室氣體吸收及發射的能量可以傳遞到其他非溫室氣體。

== 溫室氣體 ==
{{Main|溫室氣體}}
[[File:CO2_H2O_absorption_atmospheric_gases_unique_pattern_energy_wavelengths_of_energy_transparent_to_others.png|500px]]

若以對地球溫室效應的影響來排名，前四名的氣體是<ref name="realclimate.org">{{cite web| url=http://www.realclimate.org/index.php?p=142| date=6 April 2005| title=Water vapour: feedback or forcing?| publisher=RealClimate| accessdate=2006-05-01| archive-date=2009-04-18| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090418043001/http://realclimate.org/index.php?p=142| dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="kiehl19小零嘴唇邊勾起一抹微笑以
7"/>：
* [[水蒸氣|水蒸氣]]，36–70%（但不會列在[[溫室氣體|溫室氣體]]中）
* [[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]，9–26%
* [[甲烷|甲烷]]，4–9%
* [[臭氧|臭氧]]，3–7%

因為各氣體吸收及釋放頻譜有重疊，實務上很難去界定各氣體對温室效应的貢獻程度。非氣體也可能會造成温室效应，其中最主要的是{{le|雲輻射強迫|Cloud forcing|雲}}，雲也會吸收及釋放紅外線輻射，因此對大氣中的輻射特性也有一定影響<ref name="kiehl197">{{cite journal| url=http://www.atmo.arizona.edu/students/courselinks/spring04/atmo451b/pdf/RadiationBudget.pdf| title=Earth's Annual Global Mean Energy Budget| first=J. T.| last=Kiehl|author2=Kevin E. Trenberth| format=PDF | journal=Bulletin of the American Meteorological Society| pages=197–208| volume=78| issue=2|date=February 1997| accessdate=2006-05-01| doi=10.1175/1520-0477(1997)078<0197:EAGMEB>2.0.CO;2 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060330013311/http://www.atmo.arizona.edu/students/courselinks/spring04/atmo451b/pdf/RadiationBudget.pdf|archivedate = 2006-03-30 | bibcode=1997BAMS...78..197K| issn=1520-0477}}</ref>。

==對氣候變遷的影響==
{{main|全球暖化}}
[[File:Mauna_Loa_CO2_monthly_mean_concentration.svg|right]]，也就是大氣中的二氧化碳濃度]]

因為人類活動造成温室效应的增強稱為增強型（或{{le|人類對環境的影響|human impact on the environment|人為}}）温室效应<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.science.org.au/nova/016/016glo.htm |title=Enhanced greenhouse effect — Glossary |work=Nova |publisher=Australian Academy of Scihuman impact on the environment |date=2006 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080401065308/http://www.science.org.au/nova/016/016glo.htm |archivedate=2008-04-01 |deadurl=yes |accessdate=2016-08-19 |language=en }}</ref>。人類活動對[[輻射驅動力|輻射驅動力]]的增加是造成大氣中二氧化碳增加的原因<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ace.mmu.ac.uk/eae/Global_Warming/Older/Enhanced_Greenhouse_Effect.html |title=Enhanced Greenhouse Effect |publisher=Ace.mmu.ac.uk |accessdate=2010-10-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101024121935/http://www.ace.mmu.ac.uk/eae/global_warming/Older/Enhanced_Greenhouse_Effect.html |archivedate=2010-10-24 }}</ref>。根據最近[[政府間氣候變化專門委員會|政府間氣候變化專門委員會]]的評估報告「大氣中二氧化碳、甲烷及一氧化氮的濃度已到達過去八十萬年來史前無例的程度，這些氣體的影響以及其他人為作用已影響了氣候系統，可能是二十世紀以來觀察到暖化現的主要原因。」<ref>IPCC Fifth Assessment Report [http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar5/syr/AR5_SYR_FINAL_SPM.pdf Synthesis Report: Summary for Policymakers] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar5/syr/AR5_SYR_FINAL_SPM.pdf |date=20181123104020 }} (p. 4)</ref>

CO<sub>2</sub>是因為燃燒化石燃料以及其活動（例如[[水泥|水泥]]製造及[[森林開伐|熱帶森林開伐]]等）所造成<ref name="IPCC deforestation">IPCC [http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar4/wg1/ar4-wg1-chapter7.pdf Fourth Assessment Report, Working Group I Report "The Physical Science Basis"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar4/wg1/ar4-wg1-chapter7.pdf |date=20110315005004 }} Chapter 7</ref>。莫納羅亞火山天文台量測到的CO<sub>2</sub>濃度已由1960年的313ppm<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.esrl.noaa.gov/gmd/ccgg/trends/co2_data_mlo.html | title=Atmospheric Carbon Dioxide – Mauna Loa | publisher=NOAA | accessdate=2016-08-19 | archive-date=2019-05-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190520204843/https://www.esrl.noaa.gov/gmd/ccgg/trends/co2_data_mlo.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>到2010年的389 ppm。在2013年5月9日已到達400 ppm的里程碑<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/energy/2013/05/130510-earth-co2-milestone-400-ppm/ |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2016-08-19 |archive-date=2013-12-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215081625/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/energy/2013/05/130510-earth-co2-milestone-400-ppm/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。目前觀測到的CO<sub>2</sub>濃度已超過冰核心數據中的地質紀錄最大值（約300 ppm）<ref>{{cite journal |author=Hansen J. |title=A slippery slope: How much global warming constitutes "dangerous anthropogenic interference"?  |journal=Climatic Change |volume=68 |issue=333 |pages=269–279 |date=February 2005 |doi=10.1007/s10584-005-4135-0 }}</ref>。因燃燒產生二氧化碳對整體氣候的影響是第一個提出的温室效应，是[[斯凡特·奥古斯特·阿伦尼乌斯|斯凡特·奥古斯特·阿伦尼乌斯]]在1896年提出<!--has also been called the [[Callendar_effect|Callendar effect]].-->。

在過去的八十萬年之間<ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/5314592.stm | work=BBC News | title=Deep ice tells long climate story | date=2006-09-04 | accessdate=2010-05-04 | archive-date=2012-12-30 | archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6DIDU5ueW?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/5314592.stm | dead-url=no }}</ref>，冰核心數據中的二氧化碳紀錄最低值有到180 ppm，在工業革命前到270 ppm<ref>{{cite journal |author=Hileman B |title=Ice Core Record Extended |journal=Chemical & Engineering News |volume=83 |issue=48 |page=7 |date=2005-11-28 |url=http://pubs.acs.org/cen/news/83/i48/8348notw1.html |access-date=2016-08-19 |archive-date=2019-05-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190515033556/http://pubs.acs.org/cen/news/83/i48/8348notw1.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[古氣候學|古氣候學]]認為二氧化碳的變化是在這個時間尺度下造成氣候變異的主要因素<ref name="Bowen (2005), Thin Ice">Bowen, Mark; Thin Ice: Unlocking the Secrets of Climate in the World's Highest Mountains; Owl Books, 2005.</ref><ref>[http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/paleo/globalwarming/temperature-change.html Temperature change and carbon dioxide change] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/paleo/globalwarming/temperature-change.html |date=20170118144841 }}, U.S. National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration</ref>。

==真正的溫室==

[[Image:RHSGlasshouse.JPG|thumb]]]]

温室效应取名自受太陽照射而暖和的[[溫室|溫室]]。許多來源的解釋提到[[溫室|溫室]]中較高的溫度是因為太陽的[[紫外線|紫外線]]、可見光及[[红外线|红外线]]透過玻璃照到溫室內，由溫室中的地板及內容物吸收，因為溫度較高，因此會發射波長較長的紅外線。玻璃及溫室中用的其他材料無法讓紅外線穿透，因此紅外線無法透過[[輻射轉移|輻射轉移]]離開溫室。而溫室是密閉空間，因此也無法透過[[对流传热|对流传热]]的方式將熱傳遞到界，溫室內的室溫因此而提高<ref>A Dictionary of Physics (6 ed.), Oxford University Press, 2009, ISBN  9780199233991: "greenhouse effect"</ref><ref>A Dictionary of Chemistry (6 ed.), edited by John Daintith, Publisher: Oxford University Press, 2008, ISBN 9780199204632: "greenhouse effect"</ref>。温室效应是因為會吸收紅外線的[[溫室氣體|溫室氣體]]（例如二氧化碳及甲烷）其作用和溫室中的玻璃相近。而且地球也沒有夠多的空氣離開地球，因此也不會進行對流傳熱。

不過地球的温室效应和溫室中使室溫變高的效應是不同的，溫室不是因為溫室效應才使室溫變高<ref>{{cite book
 | title = Favorite demonstrations for college science: an NSTA Press journals collection
 | edition = 
 | author = Brian Shmaefsky
 | publisher = NSTA Press
 | date = 2004
 | isbn = 978-0-87355-242-4
 | page = 57
 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=L4jtv2mX0iQC&pg=PA57
 | access-date = 2016-08-19
 | archive-date = 2020-08-02
 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200802185702/https://books.google.com/books?id=L4jtv2mX0iQC&pg=PA57
 | dead-url = no
 }}</ref>。
温室室溫升高的原因主要是讓陽光照射到溫室中，而室內無法經過對流將熱傳到外界。溫室效應讓地球變熱的原因是因為溫室氣體吸收輻射能，使大氣變溫暖，再將其中的部份能量再發射回地面。

温室會以可以讓陽光通過的材料製造，多半是塑膠或是玻璃，其中室溫提高的原因是因為陽光溫暖温室內的地面及內容物，再間接的使室溫提高。因為温室內是密閉空間，因此空氣溫度會繼續上昇，和室外熱空氣會上昇，和冷空氣混合的情形不同。若將溫室的一個小窗戶打開，室內溫度會快速下降。[[羅伯特·伍德|羅伯特·伍德]]曾在1909年進行實驗，用[[石鹽|石鹽]]（紅外線可以穿透的材質）作為溫室的材料，若温室的玻璃無法讓紅外線通過是因温室室溫升高的原因，用石鹽作的温室應該無此效果，不過其室溫和玻璃作的温室類似<ref name="wood1909">{{cite journal |author=Wood, R.W. |title=Note on the Theory of the Greenhouse |journal=Philosophical Magazine |volume=17 |pages=319–320 |date=1909 |url=http://www.wmconnolley.org.uk/sci/wood_rw.1909.html |quote=When exposed to sunlight the temperature rose gradually to 65 °C., the enclosure covered with the salt plate keeping a little ahead of the other because it transmitted the longer waves from the Sun, which were stopped by the glass. In order to eliminate this action the sunlight was first passed through a glass plate."  "it is clear that the rock-salt plate is capable of transmitting practically all of it, while the glass plate stops it entirely. This shows us that the loss of temperature of the ground by radiation is very small in comparison to the loss by convection, in other words that we gain very little from the circumstance that the radiation is trapped. |doi=10.1080/14786440208636602 |access-date=2016-08-19 |archive-date=2011-08-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110807115809/http://www.wmconnolley.org.uk/sci/wood_rw.1909.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。因此溫室的原理是因為阻止室內空氣和室外[[對流|對流]]，因此使得室溫變高<ref name="Schroeder">
{{Cite book
| author=Schroeder, Daniel V.
| title=An introduction to thermal physics
| url=https://archive.org/details/introductiontoth0000schr_k1f1
| date=2000
| publisher=[[艾迪生韦斯利|Addison-Wesley]]
| location=[[旧金山|旧金山]]
| isbn=0-321-27779-1
| quote=... this mechanism is called the ''greenhouse effect'', even though most greenhouses depend primarily on a different mechanism (namely, limiting convective cooling).
| pages=[https://archive.org/details/introductiontoth0000schr_k1f1/page/305 305]–7}}
</ref><ref>{{cite book |author1=Oort, Abraham H. |author2=Peixoto, José Pinto |title=Physics of climate |publisher=American Institute of Physics |location=New York |date=1992 |isbn=0-88318-711-6 |quote=...the name water vapor-greenhouse effect is actually a misnomer since heating in the usual greenhouse is due to the reduction of convection}}</ref>。

許多現在的量化研究指出温室中避免紅外線輻射傳熱的效果雖不是溫室原理的主因，但其傳熱也有一定的量。在温室效率的經濟考量上仍有一定的影響。有研究在溫室內部中貼上對紅外線高反射係數的幕，研究近紅外線的輻射，發現熱量的需求減少了8%，研究也建議用染料塗在透明的表面上<!--Composite less-reflective glass, or less effective but cheaper anti-reflective coated simple glass, also produced savings.--><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://uwm.edu.pl/wnt/technicalsc/tech_17_4/b04.pdf |title=> ENERGY EFFECTS DURING USING THE GLASS WITH DIFFERENT PROPERTIES IN A HEATED GREENHOUSE, Sławomir Kurpaska, Technical Sciences 17(4), 2014, 351–360 |accessdate=2016-08-19 |archive-date=2015-11-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117063657/http://uwm.edu.pl/wnt/technicalsc/tech_17_4/b04.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 其他星球的温室效应 ==
在[[太陽系|太陽系]]中，[[火星|火星]]和[[金星#大氣層和氣候|金星]]也有溫室效應。金星的大氣主要成份是二氧化碳，因此温室效应相當显著。<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1126/science.11538492 | title = The greenhouse and antigreenhouse effects on Titan | year = 1991 | last1 = McKay | first1 = C. | last2 = Pollack | first2 = J. | last3 = Courtin | first3 = R. | journal = Science | volume = 253 | issue = 5024 | pages = 1118–1121| pmid=11538492}}</ref>[[土卫六|土卫六]]的大氣會吸收太陽輻射，但不會吸收紅外線的輻射，因此會有[[反温室效应|反温室效应]]，使得其氣溫下降<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.astrobio.net/news/modules.php?op=modload&name=News&file=article&sid=1762&mode=thread&order=0&thold=0 |title=Titan: Greenhouse and Anti-greenhouse :: Astrobiology Magazine - earth science - evolution distribution Origin of life universe - life beyond :: Astrobiology is study of earth |publisher=Astrobio.net |accessdate=2010-10-15 |archive-date=2020-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200722145751/https://www.astrobio.net/news-briefs/?op=modload&file=article&sid=1762&mode=thread&order=0&thold=0 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[冥王星大气层|冥王星大气层]]溫度也比預期的要冷，因為其中氮的蒸發使大氣冷卻<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/060103_pluto_cold.html |title=Pluto Colder Than Expected |publisher=SPACE.com |date=2006-01-03 |accessdate=2010-10-15 |archive-date=2010-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100516110327/http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/060103_pluto_cold.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

若温室效应中的[[正反馈|正反馈]]造成溫室氣體全部蒸發進入大氣中，稱為[[失控温室效应|失控温室效应]]<ref name=Kasting_1991>{{cite conference | first = James F. | last = Kasting | title = Runaway and moist greenhouse atmospheres and the evolution of Earth and Venus. | booktitle = Planetary Sciences: American and Soviet Research/Proceedings from the U.S.-U.S.S.R. Workshop on Planetary Sciences | pages = 234–245 | publisher = Commission on Engineering and Technical Systems (CETS) | date = 1991 | url = http://books.nap.edu/openbook.php?record_id=1790&page=234 | accessdate = 2009 | archive-date = 2011-06-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110607101819/http://books.nap.edu/openbook.php?record_id=1790&page=234 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。金星之所以会有超高的表面气温，便是由于超高的二氧化碳浓度导致的失控温室效应<ref>{{cite journal | pages = 1037–1039 | issue = 5250 | volume = 226 | date=Jun 1970 | doi = 10.1038/2261037a0| pmid = 16057644| issn = 0028-0836 | journal = Nature | first2 = C. | first1 = I. | title = The Runaway Greenhouse and the Accumulation of CO<sub>2</sub> in the Venus Atmosphere| last1 = Rasool | format = | last2 = De Bergh |bibcode = 1970Natur.226.1037R }}</ref>。

